The paper deals with face recognition using deep learning-based methods, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the generation of high-quality images using various techniques, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the reduction of domain gap between NIR and VIS data, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the security and privacy implications of face recognition, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
